description: {"blocks":[{"key":"c7ckc","text":"This protocol describes the preparation of primary neuronal cultures from E15.5 CD-1 wild type mouse embryos. Experiments involving animal models must be performed in accordance with relevant institutional guidelines and regulations.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"f04cv","text":"Remove the uterus from the abdominal cavity and place into a 10 cm sterile Petri dish on ice containing dissection medium, consisting of Hanks’ balanced salt solution (HBSS) supplemented with 0.01 M HEPES, 0.01 M MgSO4 and 1% penicillin/streptomycin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5qt1e","text":"Isolate each embryo, decapitate the heads, remove the brains from the skull and immerse in ice-cold dissection medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4712n","text":"Dissect cortical hemispheres, and remove meninges under a dissection microscope.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"be824","text":"Collect the cortices in a 15 mL sterile tube and digest with 0.25% trypsin containing 1 mM ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA) and 15 μL 0.1% DNAse I for 20 min at 37 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3rq3h","text":"Stop digestion by removing the supernatant and washing the tissue twice with Neurobasal medium (Invitrogen) containing 5% Fetal Bovine Serum.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6e4gj","text":"Resuspend the tissue in 2 mL Neurobasal medium and triturate to achieve a single cell suspension.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2745h","text":"Spin cells at 130 x g, remove the supernatant, and resuspend the cell pellet in Neurobasal medium with 2% B-27 supplement (Invitrogen), 1% L-glutamine (Invitrogen) and 1% penicillin/streptomycin (Invitrogen).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fiqq8","text":"Plate cells at desired density in dishes or coverslips coated with 1 mg/mL poly-D-lysine (Sigma) and 1 µg/mL laminin (Thermo Fisher Scientific).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Primary neuronal cultures
